%%{init: { 'theme': 'default', 'themeVariables': { 'background': '#f8fafc', 'primaryColor': '#e0f2fe', 'lineColor': '#475569' }}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    actor U as Client Browser (Web App)
    participant N as API Gateway (Reverse Proxy)
    participant R as API Router (Controller)
    participant A as Security Middleware
    participant B as Business Logic Service
    participant DB as Relational Database

    Note over U, R: Phase 1: Failed Request (Expired Access Token)
    U->>N: HTTP GET /api/protected-route (Authorization Bearer)
    N->>R: Proxy Pass to Application Server
    R->>A: Trigger Access Token Validation
    A->>A: Validation Failed: Token Expired
    A-->>R: Return 401 Unauthorized
    R-->>N: HTTP 401 Response
    N-->>U: HTTP 401 Unauthorized

    Note over U, DB: Phase 2: 401 Interception & Silent Refresh Mechanism
    U->>N: HTTP POST /api/auth/refresh (HttpOnly Cookie)
    N->>R: Proxy Pass to Application Server
    R->>A: Validate Refresh Token from Cookie
    A->>A: Extract and Verify Refresh Token
    A->>DB: Check Revocation Status (Blacklist)
    activate DB
    DB-->>A: Token Valid (Not Revoked)
    deactivate DB
    A->>DB: Insert Old Token into Blacklist (Revocation)
    A->>A: Generate New Access Token & Refresh Token
    A-->>R: Return New Credentials
    R-->>N: HTTP 200 OK (New Tokens)
    N-->>U: Save New Access Token to Client Memory

    Note over U, B: Phase 3: Automatic Retry of Initial Request
    U->>N: HTTP GET /api/protected-route (NEW Authorization Bearer)
    N->>R: Proxy Pass to Application Server
    R->>A: Trigger Access Token Validation
    A->>A: Validation Success: Token Valid
    A-->>R: Return Token Payload (User ID)
    R->>B: Execute Requested Endpoint
    activate B
    B->>DB: Resource Ownership Validation (owner_id == user_id)
    activate DB
    DB-->>B: Confirm Access Rights
    deactivate DB
    B-->>R: Return Requested Data
    deactivate B
    R-->>N: HTTP 200 OK (JSON Data)
    N-->>U: HTTP 200 OK (Data is rendered in UI)